title: MacArthur holds on to beat Churchill
text:

Close
Image 1 of 1 MacArthur quarterback Tyler Vitt rushes for the end zone, but he’s pulled down by the Churchill defense. Vitt finished 11 of 17 passing for 146 yards.
Photo: Jena Stopczynski /For The Express-News MacArthur quarterback Tyler Vitt rushes for the end zone, but... MacArthur holds on to beat Churchill 1 / 1 Back to Gallery After seeming to have the game in hand, MacArthur sweated out the final minutes to beat Churchill 35-28 on Friday at Heroes Stadium.
The Brahmas led 35-14 late in the fourth quarter before the Chargers were able to pull within two scores on a 78-yard pass play from Devon Faktor to De’Andre Reed. A successful onside kick later, and Churchill was back in business. Seven plays later it was a touchdown difference after another Faktor touchdown, this one for 7 yards to Jordan Billups in the corner of the end zone.
The ensuing onside kick appeared to go in Churchill’s favor before an illegal touching penalty gave the ball back to MacArthur.
The Brahmas (5-1, 2-0) were able to run out the clock and secure a perfect start to 26-6A play.
